ame of democracy, found an enthusiastic audience for their bold populist rhetoric among wide swathes of society. In Amnesia, Arjun Subrahmanyan illustrates how the idealism of the first decade of Thai democracy, now largely forgotten, still shapes Thai society.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Mrz 2024) 0aDemocracy-Thailand-History. 0aThailand-Politics and government. 4aAnthropology and Archaeology : Anthropology. 4aAsian Studies : Asian Studies. 4aHistory : History. 4aPolitics and Law : Democracy. 4aPolitics and Law : Political Science. 7aHISTORY / Asia / Southeast Asia.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2021z978311149169140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143848652940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438486529423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438486529/original  a978-3-11-149169-1  SUNY Press eBook Package 2021b2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles